article.description: Demonte Flannigan scored with 1.8 seconds left and Cleveland State held back Belmont's late rally for a 67-65 victory on Saturday.
article.headline: Cleveland State scores with 1.8 left, beats Belmont 67-65
article.linkText: Cleveland State scores with 1.8 left, beats Belmont 67-65
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Demonte Flannigan scored with 1.8 seconds left and Cleveland State held back Belmont's late rally for a 67-65 victory on Saturday. Mack Mercer made a pair of free throws to cap Belmont's 19-4 run and the Bruins led 65-63 with 49 seconds to play. Flannigan scored a running hook shot to tie it at 65. Mercer, who scored a game-high 20 points, then missed a jumper. The Vikings' Andre Yates took the inbound pass at midcourt with 4.3 seconds to go, and passed to Flannigan in the low post. Flannigan spun and shot a left-handed layup off the glass for the game-winner. Belmont (7-6) threw a pass down court and it was knocked down under the basket to end it. Daniel Levitt made a 3 to give Cleveland State (4-7) a 59-46 lead with nine minutes left. Flannigan scored eight of his 16 points and had two rebounds with and a block in the final seven minutes.
